From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Mon, 2 Oct 2023 17:43:15 +0200
Subject: scsi: bnx2fc: Do not rely on a SCSI command for LUN or target reset
Git-commit: 6a137a967bc7da58f8e304c96af1df947f13e52c
Patch-mainline: v6.7-rc1
References: jsc#PED-11312

When a LUN or target reset is issued, we should not rely on a SCSI command
to be present; we'll have to reset the entire device or target anyway.

